1:1 COMMENT "# generator_intrange.z -- parameter-driven generator."
1:54 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# `intrange` yields i64 values from `lo` (inclusive) up to `hi`"
3:64 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# (exclusive). The straight-line body uses a captured loop counter;"
4:68 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# the compiler promotes `i` (yield-crossing) to a field on the synth"
5:69 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# class `intrange_iter` and drives it via the state machine. The"
6:65 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# `lo`/`hi` valtype parameters become value fields on the same"
7:63 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# class."
8:9 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "#"
9:2 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "# Demonstrates: out-only generator with multiple captured params"
10:65 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "# and a yielding loop. See doc/spec.pdoc Generator functions."
11:62 EOL "\n"
12:1 EOL "\n"
